│ subtle bugs in LLVM's optimization passes, as operand        │
│ bundles are a less common feature.                           │
│                                                              │
│ 3. **Root Cause Analysis**: The `foldShuffleToIdentity`      │
│ function is likely not the source of the bug but rather the  │
│ victim of a previously applied incorrect transformation. The │
│ `InstSimplify` library, which performs many common           │
│ simplifications, has logic to simplify                       │
│ `shufflevector(call(...))` patterns. However, this logic     │
│ does not correctly handle cases where the `call` instruction │
│ has operand bundles. This oversight leads to the creation of │
│ malformed IR. When `vector-combine` later processes this IR, │
│ it encounters an instruction with an invalid type, leading   │
