│ An LLVM `InstSimplify` optimization attempts to transform    │
│ `shuffle(call)` into `call(shuffle)`. However, this          │
│ transformation fails to correctly propagate operand bundles  │
│ from the original `call` instruction to the newly created    │
│ one. This oversight results in the generation of malformed   │
│ LLVM IR.                                                     │
│                                                              │
│ When a subsequent pass, such as `vector-combine`, processes  │
│ this malformed IR, it encounters an instruction with an      │
│ invalid type, leading to a crash. The crash occurs because   │
│ the pass expects a `FixedVectorType` but finds a different   │
│ type due to the incorrect simplification.                    │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to disable this specific `shuffle(call)`          │
│ optimization when the `call` instruction has operand         │
│ bundles. This is achieved by adding a check `if              │
│ (CI->hasOperandBundles())` and bailing out of the            │
│ transformation if it returns true. This prevents the         │
│ creation of the malformed IR and resolves the subsequent     │
│ crash.                                                       │
│                                                              │
│ To apply the fix, I will add the check at the beginning of   │
│ the `shuffle(call) -> call(shuffle)` logic in                │
│ `llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp`.                 │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_code>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file": "llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp",     │
│     "old": "  // shuffle(call) -> call(shuffle)\n  if (auto  │
│ *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(V1)) {\n    // We can't just move   │
│ the shuffle through the call if the call has side\n    //    │
│ effects.\n    if (!CI->onlyReadsMemory() &&                  │
│ !CI->doesNotAccessMemory())\n      return std::nullopt;",    │
│     "new": "  // shuffle(call) -> call(shuffle)\n  if (auto  │
│ *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(V1)) {\n    // We can't handle      │
│ operand bundles yet.\n    if (CI->hasOperandBundles())\n     │
